      <!-- ═══ USAGE TAB ═══ -->
      <div class="tab-content" id="tab-usage" style="display: none; padding-top: 32px;">

        <!-- When and Where to Use -->
        <div class="doc-section">
          <h2 id="when-to-use" class="doc-section-title">When and Where to Use</h2>
          <p class="doc-section-subtitle">Counters communicate numeric quantities at a glance, always paired with contextual labels or parent components.</p>

          <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 24px; margin-top: 24px;">
            <div style="padding: 24px; background: var(--prism-surface); border: 1px solid var(--prism-border); border-radius: 12px; transition: all 0.25s ease;">
              <h3 id="when-to-use-details" style="font-size: 15px; font-weight: 600; color: var(--prism-text); margin-bottom: 16px; display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 8px;">
                <svg width="20" height="20" fill="none" stroke="#2563eb" stroke-width="2" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7"/></svg>
                When to use
              </h3>
              <ul class="doc-list" style="border: none; background: transparent; padding-left: 20px; font-size: 14.5px;">
                <li style="border: none; background: transparent; margin-bottom: 8px;">Display unread notification counts on navigation items.</li>
                <li style="border: none; background: transparent; margin-bottom: 8px;">Show item counts in tabs, filters, or category labels.</li>
                <li style="border: none; background: transparent; margin-bottom: 8px;">Indicate quantity in list rows or table cells.</li>
                <li style="border: none; background: transparent;">Display status-grouped counts in dashboards.</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
            <div style="padding: 24px; background: var(--prism-surface); border: 1px solid var(--prism-border); border-radius: 12px; transition: all 0.25s ease;">
              <h3 id="when-not-to-use" style="font-size: 15px; font-weight: 600; color: var(--prism-text); margin-bottom: 16px; display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 8px;">
                <svg width="20" height="20" fill="none" stroke="#e42527" stroke-width="2" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M6 18L18 6M6 6l12 12"/></svg>
                When NOT to use
              </h3>
              <ul class="doc-list" style="border: none; background: transparent; padding-left: 20px; font-size: 14.5px;">
                <li style="border: none; background: transparent; margin-bottom: 8px;">For non-numeric content (use Badge instead).</li>
                <li style="border: none; background: transparent; margin-bottom: 8px;">As a standalone status indicator (use Status Indicator).</li>
                <li style="border: none; background: transparent; margin-bottom: 8px;">For categorization labels (use Tag).</li>
                <li style="border: none; background: transparent;">When count meaning is unclear without context.</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <hr class="doc-divider" />

        <!-- Semantic States -->
        <div class="doc-section">
          <h2 id="semantic-states" class="doc-section-title">Semantic States</h2>
          <p class="doc-section-subtitle">Each state maps to a specific semantic meaning, ensuring consistent communication across the interface.</p>
          <ul class="doc-list">
            <li><strong>Active:</strong> Primary or informational counts such as unread messages, new items, or selected filters.</li>
            <li><strong>Critical:</strong> Error or failure counts indicating items requiring immediate attention (e.g., failed deployments).</li>
            <li><strong>Moderate:</strong> Warning or alert counts for situations needing review but not yet critical.</li>
            <li><strong>Important:</strong> Urgent but non-critical counts, such as overdue tasks or pending approvals.</li>
            <li><strong>Success:</strong> Completed or positive counts, like resolved tickets or successful operations.</li>
            <li><strong>Default:</strong> Neutral or secondary counts for general-purpose use without semantic weight.</li>
            <li><strong>Acknowledge:</strong> Acknowledged or informational-secondary counts, often used for dismissed or archived items.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <hr class="doc-divider" />

        <!-- Detailed Do's and Don'ts -->
        <div class="doc-section">
          <h2 id="detailed-guidelines" class="doc-section-title">Complete Do's and Don'ts</h2>
          <p class="doc-section-subtitle">Visual and interaction guidelines to ensure counters are effective, consistent, and accessible.</p>
          <div class="do-dont-grid">
            <div class="do-card"><span class="card-label">Do</span>
              <ul class="doc-list" style="border: none; background: transparent; padding: 0;">
                <li style="border: none; background: transparent; padding-left: 20px;"><strong>Keep values short:</strong> Use 1-3 digits. Display "99+" for values exceeding 99.</li>
                <li style="border: none; background: transparent; padding-left: 20px;"><strong>Provide context:</strong> Always pair counters with a parent label, icon, or navigation item.</li>
                <li style="border: none; background: transparent; padding-left: 20px;"><strong>Consistent style per group:</strong> Use either all Subtle or all Intense within a single UI row.</li>
                <li style="border: none; background: transparent; padding-left: 20px;"><strong>Match semantics:</strong> Use Critical for errors, Success for completions, Active for informational.</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="dont-card"><span class="card-label">Don't</span>
              <ul class="doc-list" style="border: none; background: transparent; padding: 0;">
                <li style="border: none; background: transparent; padding-left: 20px;"><strong>Non-numeric content:</strong> Don't display text or icons inside a Counter (use Badge instead).</li>
                <li style="border: none; background: transparent; padding-left: 20px;"><strong>Standalone use:</strong> Don't use a Counter without adjacent context explaining what is being counted.</li>
                <li style="border: none; background: transparent; padding-left: 20px;"><strong>Mixed styles:</strong> Don't mix Subtle and Intense in the same row or contextual group.</li>
                <li style="border: none; background: transparent; padding-left: 20px;"><strong>Large numbers:</strong> Don't display raw large numbers like "1542" without truncation.</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <hr class="doc-divider" />

        <!-- Related -->
        <div class="doc-section">
          <h2 id="related" class="doc-section-title">Related</h2>
          <p class="doc-section-subtitle">Components that complement or can be used alongside the Counter.</p>
